{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nA critical validation of the \"behavioral and contractual test-coverage report\" was\nre-verified against `origin/main` (commit `6244666`; findings cross-checked at the\nreport's pinned `4e0c588`). The validation is mostly correct, with two notable results:\n\n- The report's HIGH-priority claim that the concurrency-storm integration tests\n  \"self-disable via a non-strict xfail\" is **INVALID** at both commits — the preflight\n  is a functional `rebar init` probe (`tests/integration/test_store_concurrency.py`),\n  not the \"executable-under-repo-root\" check the report describes, so a correct\n  editable install gates CI normally. **No work is scheduled for that finding.**\n- The remaining valid findings are genuine and are collected here. They cluster around\n  compaction fault-atomicity, process-level durability contracts, a real\n  (vs simulated) remote-append interleaving, input validation, docs drift, and\n  test-suite hygiene.\n\nPolicy decisions resolved for this epic:\n- **Whitespace-only ticket titles must be rejected** (current `if not title` in\n  `src/rebar/_commands/composer.py` accepts them).\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Every valid finding from the validation is either fixed or has a scheduled child\n  story, and each invalid finding is explicitly excluded (documented above).\n- The compaction fold is provably all-or-none under forward- and reverse-rename\n  failure, and recoverable after real process death.\n- The async-push, remote-append, and parent-cascade contracts have tests that exercise\n  the actual process/clone-level behavior, not in-process simulations.\n- Stale docs (concurrency.md detached-HEAD claim, README `flock` framing,\n  mutation-doc scope wording) are corrected.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nEach item below is a repo-observable end-state (verifiable by a command or artifact),\nnot a process milestone. This epic closes when every child is closed (rebar enforces the\nopen-children guard), i.e. `rebar deps <epic>` shows no open descendants.\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` no longer unconditionally removes the snapshot in\n      its rollback branch; a fault-injection test asserting snapshot retention on\n      incomplete rollback exists and passes.\n- [ ] `rebar create`/`edit` and the library/MCP create paths reject a whitespace-only\n      title (a test passing `\"   \"` asserts an error) across CLI, library, and MCP.\n- [ ] `docs/concurrency.md` references the detached-HEAD regression test,\n      `README.md` describes the `fcntl`+`mkdir` lock (no external `flock`), and\n      `docs/mutation-testing.md` scopes its scores to the five cores.\n- [ ] New tests exist for: compaction rename fault injection, compactor process death,\n      async-push parent-exit survival, real remote-append interleaving, and\n      parent-cascade cross-clone races (grep-able test names present in the suite).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on the merged result."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783887509731293001,"uuid":"4915a7db-7bc0-43a8-889a-5eeaf3bff1a4"}